frameDefinitions: The words in this frame involve an Undesirable_event which affects the Patient negatively.

This frame concerns an Addict's physiological or psychological compulsive dependence on an Addictant, the substance or behavior to which the Addict is addicted. '' 'Although she was never a big fan of drugs, she became hooked on that designer drug instantly.'
A Perpetrator (generally intentionally) commits a Crime, i.e. does something not permitted by the laws of society.
A trial is a process conducted in a Court before a Judge and (usually) a Jury in which the participants meet in order to decide a Case.
Words in this frame describe acts in violation of a legal code.

This is an abstract frame for durative activities, in which the Agent enters an ongoing state of the Activity, remains in this state for some Duration of Time, and leaves this state either by finishing or by stopping.
frameExamples: The first <t>calamity</t> was a disastrous trade war with Holland.
Although she was never a big fan of drugs, she became <t>hooked</t> on that designer drug instantly.
They <t>perpetrated</t> a felony by substituting a lie for negotiations.
He was accused of <t><fex name='Offense'>hijacking</fex></t> a tour bus full of people.
listRoleDefinitions: The undesirable event which occurs.
The entity that experiences the <fen>Undesirable_Event</fen>.
When the <fen>Undesirable_Event</fen> occurs.
Where the <fen>Undesirable_Event</fen> takes place.
The <fen>Addict</fen> is physiologically or psychologically dependent on a substance or a behavior.
<fen>Addictant</fen> is the substance or behavior to which the <fen>Addict</fen> is dependent.
The individual that commits a <fen>Crime</fen>.
When the <fen>Crime</fen> was committed.
The location where the <fen>Crime</fen> occurs.
The legal label for the crime that the <fen>Defendant</fen> is accused of.
The specific room where the participants in a Trial meet.

The individual or group which is responsible for promoting the welfare of the  <fen>Defendant</fen> during a Trial, usually involving the contention that the <fen>Defendant</fen> is innocent of the <fen>Charges</fen>.
The group of individuals who observe the Trial and ultimately attempt to come to a verdict.
The individual or group responsible for promoting the interests of the state in the Trial, prototypically including presenting arguments for the guilt of the <fen>Defendant</fen>.
The person charged with an offence.
The official who directs and presides over the Trial.
The <fen>Case</fen> which a Trial is convened to decide.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the trial occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the trial occurs.
The illegal act.
This role denotes the person or entity that is badly affected by the <fen>Offense</fen>.
The individual who commits the Offense
The <fen>Agent</fen> is engaged in the <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Activity</fen> occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Activity</fen> occurs.
listRoleExamples: An <fex>environmental</fex> disaster is just what we need.
How can <fex>he</fex> commit treason against the King of England in a foreign country , if he is not English?
A murder perpetrated <fex>at 1:08AM this morning</fex> was not investigated until noon today.
We have jurisdiction over crimes committed <fex>in Woodside County</fex>.
The police is investigating the homicide <fex>of Dr. Johnson</fex>.
